  "description": "Modeled coastal flood hazard zone for 100-year storm inundation extent.",
  "abstract": "<p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:1.5rem; font-family:&quot;Avenir Next W01&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next W00&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:16px;'>Coastal flood hazard zones were developed by 3 different external expert consultants in 2020. The layers are derived by advanced models using empirical calculations including tide gauge and extreme water level analysis, wind records and wave models, and used the 2019 LiDAR DEM.</p><span style='font-family:&quot;Avenir Next W01&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next W00&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:16px;'>Three different models were used to construct the coastal flood layers: a full-coastline ‘bathtub model’ (Tonkin and Taylor, 2020), and two hydrodynamic models for Rangaunu (eCoast, 2020) and Kaipara (DHI, 2019) harbors. The reports detailing the methodologies can be accessed from the NRC website.</span>",
